http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/Tata-Steel-shelves-Bastar-project/article14594751.ece

Tata Steel has decided to withdraw from its proposed 5.5 million tonne integrated steel plant project in Lohandiguda area of Maoist insurgency-hit Bastar region of Chhattisgarh.Tata Steel’s Chhattisgarh project head Anil Sinha said that the decision (to pull out of Bastar steel plant) was taken in the month of February-March this year. “It is officially confirmed. We have decided to withdraw because we could not convert prospecting into mining lease.”